When an InputSource is processed that only has a document, but no URI set, a
NullPointerException is thrown. The following patch corrects this.

--- xml-batik\sources/org/apache/batik/transcoder/SVGAbstractTranscoder.java
2003-10-31 16:39:42.000000000 +0100
+++
xml-batik-1.5.1\sources/org/apache/batik/transcoder/SVGAbstractTranscoder.java
2004-04-11 18:06:06.691136000 +0200
@@ -247,7 +247,7 @@

         // compute the preserveAspectRatio matrix
         AffineTransform Px;
-        String ref = new ParsedURL(uri).getRef();
+        String ref = uri == null ? null : new ParsedURL(uri).getRef();

         try {
             Px = ViewBox.getViewTransform(ref, root, width, height);
